dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.tip.nrf.TrafficConditioningProfile
dataStructure.description:
This object class represents a collection of attributes, which are used to define the traffic conditioning parameters (e.g., bandwidth characteristics) on a Termination Point (TP). See R_TMF518_NRF_I_0052, R_TMF518_NRF_I_0053 and R_TMF518_NRF_I_0054.

This entity is optional

This entity is extendable

This entity generates Object Creation notifications

This entity generates Object Deletion notifications

This entity generates Object Discovery notifications

This entity generates Attribute Value Change notifications.
dataStructure.label: TrafficConditioningProfile

child.name: isDefaultProfile
child.description:
This attribute defines the TC Profile as a non-deleteable profile.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is invariant

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC disabled
child.label: isDefaultProfile

child.name: layeredTrafficConditioningParameterList
child.description:
This attribute represents a list of traffic conditioning parameters which can be set and/or retrieved at a specified connectionless layer on a Termination Point (TP) having this TC Profile assigned. Refer to chapter "Traffic conditioning parameters" of the supporting document SD1-16_LayeredParameters for details of the currently defined traffic conditioning parameters

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC enabled
child.label: layeredTrafficConditioningParameterList
